1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 4=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:36,590
Ms. He,

4
00:00:36,790 --> 00:00:38,320
I owe you my life again.

5
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:40,240
I'll treat you to hotpot.

6
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:42,110
You should feel ashamed.

7
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:43,710
You still owe me tons of movies.

8
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:47,430
We are pretty blessed.

9
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:49,560
No, that's not it.

10
00:00:49,710 --> 00:00:52,470
It's Ms. He sweeping in from the sky.

11
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:54,230
Right?

12
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:57,440
Ms. He,

13
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:59,070
weren't you stationed overseas?

14
00:00:59,070 --> 00:01:00,880
Chen didn't say you were coming back.

15
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:02,190
Yeah.

16
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:03,670
When did you get back?

17
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:04,940
Just got here.

18
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:07,310
Wanted to see if Chen Youxi was dead.

19
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:10,200
He's still alive and kicking.

20
00:01:10,830 --> 00:01:11,680
Ms. He,

21
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,710
how did you even know we were there?

22
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,510
I called the museum.

23
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:16,790
Curator Zhu told me.

24
00:01:16,950 --> 00:01:18,200
You knew about the temple too?

25
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,760
The receptionist at your inn told me.

26
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,430
So, I hired a local guide.

27
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:23,620
He led me straight there.

28
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:27,590
Ms. He really lives up to her name.

29
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:29,070
Look at that quick thinking.

30
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,280
We never thought

31
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,760
of hiring a local guide.

32
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,350
We didn't have that kind of cash.

33
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,310
So stingy.

34
00:01:36,150 --> 00:01:38,120
Then how did you know
we were trapped inside?

35
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,680
When I got there, I saw two groups.

36
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:43,040
One group was fully armed.

37
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:46,000
The other was an old man.

38
00:01:48,510 --> 00:01:50,430
That's right; it was him.

39
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,680
You've met him too?

40
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,680
We nearly died because of him.

41
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,590
You found us by following him?

42
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,600
Yeah.

43
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:01,920
Next time,

44
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:04,400
don't tail strangers so easily.

45
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,560
It's way too risky.

46
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,000
Unlike someone,

47
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,710
I don't get trapped in a tunnel.

48
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:18,580
(Huayuan Inn)

49
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,280
Curator Zhu told you we're staying here?

50
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:24,550
Yeah.

51
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,590
So, what's the plan now?

52
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,520
What plan?

53
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,030
Let's just head back.

54
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:31,710
Go yourself if you want.

55
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,960
We're not leaving.

56
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,080
You've got no sense, do you?

57
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,870
There's a group of armed men

58
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:39,080
chasing right behind us,

59
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,400
and you still won't hide?

60
00:02:41,150 --> 00:02:42,680
Chen, say something.

61
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,590
You guys go get some rest.

62
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,910
I'll give Curator Zhu a call.

63
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,180
- I'll go too.
- Sure.

64
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,080
What? Guns and explosives?

65
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:52,920
Yeah.

66
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,560
There are quite a few of them.

67
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:55,800
They're heavily armed.

68
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,590
From what we've seen before,

69
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,430
they're not just tomb raiders.

70
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,430
I'll report this new finding right away.

71
00:03:03,746 --> 00:03:04,805
Hold your position for now.

72
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:05,710
Stay on standby.

73
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,360
What did he say?

74
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,386
He'll call the police.

75
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,280
The local cops will hear about it soon.

76
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,960
Let's go.

77
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,910
That old man's really the tomb keeper?

78
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:20,750
Yeah.

79
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,260
He should be the tomb keeper.

80
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,766
We also found an ancient painting

81
00:03:24,777 --> 00:03:25,520
at his place.

82
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,146
Lu examined it and said

83
00:03:27,157 --> 00:03:28,577
that it's from the mid-Tang dynasty.

84
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,840
The shoes worn by the woman in it

85
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:32,430
have the same pattern

86
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,520
as my embroidered ones.

87
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:38,150
Are you going to keep exploring
the tomb?

88
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:40,840
For duty,

89
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,430
I don't want our relics

90
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,710
to end up with someone else.

91
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,470
For myself,

92
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,000
I want to figure out

93
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,280
what the eye mark on my body

94
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,680
really means.

95
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,840
Want to hear what I think?

96
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,870
You're just trying to talk me out of it.

97
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:56,983
I couldn't stop you anyway.

98
00:03:57,319 --> 00:03:59,592
Otherwise, you'd have come abroad
with me for treatment.

99
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:02,120
Doctors can't cure what I've got.

100
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:04,750
Chubby and Lu insisted on coming along

101
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:06,080
for some hope.

102
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,560
We gave it a last shot.

103
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,960
You saw it yourself today.

104
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,080
If you hadn't rushed in on time,

105
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,520
we might not have made it out.

106
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,190
I don't want my mess

107
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,560
to cost their lives.

108
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,750
First of all,

109
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,920
those people don't know
where the tomb's entrance is.

110
00:04:25,059 --> 00:04:26,992
Otherwise, they wouldn't be
blasting everywhere.

111
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,600
Plus, the police already know,

112
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,040
so you don't need to worry

113
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,480
about them stealing the treasure.

114
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,800
Second, Professor Chen's condition

115
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,870
has improved a lot.

116
00:04:36,726 --> 00:04:38,142
I think you can come abroad with me

117
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:39,070
to try a new treatment.

118
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:42,680
Maybe it'll actually cure you.

119
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,270
You'll never know unless you try.

120
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:47,800
If you want to come back,

121
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,040
we'll come back

122
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,360
after you get better.

123
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,360
If you want to find some answers,

124
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,560
I'll go with you.

125
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:56,230
Alright.

126
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:57,600
Deal?

127
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,030
Deal.

128
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,520
What's going on?

129
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,800
Something's wrong!

130
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,190
Something's wrong!

131
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,160
Chubby...

132
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,750
Chubby got taken away!

133
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:21,920
In that car!

134
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:23,630
They asked us

135
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:26,510
to go to the temple to save him.

136
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:27,590
What?

137
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,480
No cops, or they'll kill him.

138
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,480
There are quite a few people.

139
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:14,720
They look pretty professional.

140
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,560
They are armed and ready.

141
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,510
They can even blow up a mountain.

142
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:20,240
Who are these people?

143
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,040
Maybe mercenaries.

144
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,720
Why would they want Chubby?

145
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,870
What else could it be?

146
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,310
They want us to help them rob a tomb.

147
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:30,830
Then kill us to keep it quiet?

148
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,750
Listen to me.

149
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,720
I'll go talk to them.

150
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,800
You two stay outside.

151
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,103
That'll give us a better chance.

152
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,070
Let's go together.

153
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,160
If we all go, they'll catch us all.

154
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,870
If things go bad, call the cops.

155
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,190
Chen Youxi.

156
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:48,190
Be careful.

157
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:50,470
Don't worry.

158
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:05,680
I want to see your boss.

159
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,030
This way.

160
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,040
You're here. Why not eat something?

161
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:40,790
Where's Chubby?

162
00:07:42,370 --> 00:07:43,240
I'm here.

163
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,750
Over here, Chen.

164
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:45,800
Is that you?

165
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,800
Chen, I knew you'd show up.

166
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:56,560
It's fine. I can handle it.

167
00:07:57,897 --> 00:07:59,190
They wouldn't dare mess with me.

168
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,200
See?

169
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,480
Not a scratch on me.

170
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,510
Their food's actually decent.

171
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:05,710
Eat up.

172
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,600
Don't mind me; you go ahead.

173
00:08:11,510 --> 00:08:12,600
Nice gear.

174
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,720
How did you get these guns here?

175
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:17,720
We came in a rush this time.

176
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,120
We didn't prepare much.

177
00:08:19,263 --> 00:08:20,769
How long did you search for this tomb?

178
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:21,750
Same as you.

179
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,040
There are so many archaeologists.

180
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,510
Why keep watching me?

181
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,190
You've been to the Nether Ruins.

182
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,200
This tomb looks a bit like that one.

183
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:34,720
Among the archaeologists,

184
00:08:35,046 --> 00:08:36,412
only you have the real experience.

185
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:40,030
What if you shoot me

186
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,960
after I find the tomb?

187
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,320
Who's gonna keep Chubby and me safe?

188
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,150
Move! Hurry up!

189
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,960
Lu.

190
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:51,390
Shutong.

191
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:53,630
Chen,

192
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,960
we got caught.

193
00:08:58,150 --> 00:08:59,440
Do you even have a way out now?

194
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,240
Let me say it one more time.

195
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,720
I came all the way here

196
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,550
just to open this tomb.

197
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,510
You can have a share of the treasure.

198
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,000
It doesn't matter to me.

199
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:13,870
He Shutong,

200
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,200
you're even prettier than I imagined.

201
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,960
When I was abroad,

202
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:22,600
I once wanted to visit you,

203
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:25,440
but it didn't work out by chance.

204
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,870
I'm Bai Lingling. Nice to meet you.

205
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,840
If we're visiting and chatting,

206
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,480
why not sit down, eat, and talk?

207
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,480
I'm still starving here.

208
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:39,510
Chubby,

209
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,120
didn't we go down that tunnel?

210
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,790
Why didn't you take Miss Bai down?

211
00:09:44,670 --> 00:09:46,910
I wanted to walk arm in arm
with her too,

212
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,030
but first, my arms were tied.

213
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:50,000
How can I do that?

214
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,790
Second, those punks blew up the entry.

215
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:57,750
You jerks, just wait and see.

216
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:21,480
Don't bother.

217
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:23,412
We've scanned it with the detector.

218
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,960
The tunnel has been buried.

219
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,600
Last time we went down,

220
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:30,960
we saw the fork in the road.

221
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,000
After you blew it up,

222
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,100
it's completely blocked now.

223
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,600
Find a way out.

224
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,870
Otherwise, no one's leaving.

225
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,030
We've stayed out of the scene for years,

226
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,440
and you've messed up all the old rules.

227
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,750
We don't care about rules.

228
00:10:42,789 --> 00:10:43,872
We only care about results.

229
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:45,750
Commander Chen,
don't waste time on rules.

230
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,240
It's wilderness all over.

231
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:48,960
They're holding guns.

232
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,870
We may not make it back alive.

233
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:52,600
Don't distract him.

234
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:00,600
The Yi-Bing union finds kinship in Xu.

235
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,870
Xin-Ren waters exit at Chen.

236
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,150
Gui-Jia waters slant toward Wei.

237
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:10,750
Ding-Geng waters seek Chou.

238
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,480
Feng Shui

239
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,910
is just the ancient way
of building things.

240
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,840
These secret formulas look mysterious.

241
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,870
But honestly,

242
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,670
they're just what architects
have gathered

243
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:21,823
from centuries of experience.

244
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:24,270
I think the entrance is right ahead.

245
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,360
Are you sure?

246
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:29,990
Ms. He,

247
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:32,080
show us what you've got today.

248
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,440
Don't try any tricks.

249
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,526
You've got plenty of people here;

250
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,670
everyone's armed.

251
00:11:38,266 --> 00:11:40,239
There are just four of us;
Lu even needs oxygen.

252
00:11:40,379 --> 00:11:41,492
Are you really afraid of us?

253
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:42,480
Yeah, exactly.

254
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:43,870
My health is poor.

255
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:45,910
We wouldn't dare.

256
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,270
We'd never dare.

257
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:48,900
Then what are you waiting for?

258
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,550
It's going to be some delicate work.

259
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,870
With a small mistake,

260
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,600
even if you have an atomic bomb,

261
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:29,150
you still can't get into this tomb.

262
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,080
It's a Four Bureau Star Lock.

263
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,870
What does that mean?

264
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,840
It means

265
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,663
that beneath the temple,

266
00:12:36,674 --> 00:12:38,482
there are eight stone slabs
set by the Bagua.

267
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:39,670
Each adjacent direction

268
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:41,309
must be pressed
at the same time to open,

269
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:44,150
or the mechanism locks down completely.

270
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,680
Shutong,

271
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:50,120
you take the Qian position;
I'll take Kun.

272
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:52,480
We'll each need one person to assist.

273
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,680
Why?

274
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:56,030
Everything moves with rules.

275
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,843
All things are composed of Yin and Yang.

276
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,240
Each trigraph needs two people

277
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:00,910
to keep Yin and Yang in harmony.

278
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,040
You don't believe me?

279
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:06,990
Hold still.

280
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:08,630
What are you doing?

281
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,120
Grabbing the shovel.

282
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:11,990
Shutong,

283
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:13,600
same old rules.

284
00:13:13,866 --> 00:13:14,790
A halfway lucky number.

285
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:15,800
Three taels and two qian.

286
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:16,750
Let's start.

287
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:20,270
Green Jupiter thrives in the east.

288
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:22,440
Offending the west brings harm.

289
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,120
Red Mars dwells in the south.

290
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:26,150
Violating the north brings doom.

291
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:34,470
Come on.

292
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,120
Four earthly stations dread the wood.

293
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,790
Its presence saps their might.

294
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:41,790
Metal's home is in the west.

295
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,270
If fire arrives, it flees in fright.

296
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:45,110
One.

297
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,840
Two.

298
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:47,920
Three.

299
00:13:48,390 --> 00:13:49,630
Water's place is in the north.

300
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,390
In earthly vaults, it meets its death.

301
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,560
One.

302
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:54,110
Two.

303
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,440
Three.

304
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,320
